      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Edmondo Quattrocchi (1889-1966) was an Italian sculptor known for his monumental figures.  He worked primarily 
	  in bronze and marble.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Edmondo Quattrocchi Papers</emph> consists of photographs, correspondence, clippings, 
		 programs and other memorabilia.  Items relating to a particular piece of work is collected together, 
		 regardless of type.  The material relating to his bust of Frederick MacMonnies includes a letter from 
		 MacMonnies to Henry Ridgely Carter, which reads, "Dear Mr. Carter, In case of my death, Mr. Edmondo Quattrocchi 
		 is the man to replace me, if you can induce him to undertake the work."</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
